      <scopecontent id="aspace_a594d74bc130f34b32e0ce4f38f24055">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>New Haven Musicians is a growing collection of audio interviews with singers, songwriters and players from the New Haven area who perform in clubs, bars, coffeehouses, and other venues in the area.  Covering the 1960s to the present day, the collection features artists from across the New Haven musical community, representing a wide variety of genre and cultures that continue to impact the local music scene.</p>
      </scopecontent>
      <accessrestrict id="aspace_8d8fff2fe10bff842e8d705b92ce6747">
         <head>Conditions Governing Access</head>
         <p>This collection is open for research. The finding aid includes links to stream most interviews online Yale University Library's AV access system, Aviary. Yale users can login to Aviary using their Yale University ID, to stream these interviews without restriction. Other users are able to request access to interviews directly through Aviary. For detailed access instructions, see <ref href="https://guides.library.yale.edu/oham/collectionsguide/access">OHAM's website</ref>.</p>
         <p>Please sumbit a <ref href="https://yaleuniversity-muslib.formstack.com/forms/oham">Transcript Request</ref> to inquire about the availability of a transcript.</p>
         <p>Some interviews may be restricted. Access to these restricted interviews may only be granted to a patron who has first obtained direct permission from the interviewee or their estate.</p>
      </accessrestrict>
      <userestrict id="aspace_cfb3accf21a8eb69e244bab4478f5159">
         <head>Conditions Governing Use</head>
         <p>Rights and permissions for Oral History of American Music materials vary between individual interviews. Researchers wishing to publish or broadcast Oral History of American Music materials are responsible for obtaining direct authorization from copyright holders: generally, the interviewees or their estates.</p>
      </userestrict>
      <prefercite id="aspace_ee743a3bddd73b3f02f658c82aa8ceae">
         <head>Preferred Citation</head>
         <p>NHM, New Haven Musicians, Oral History of American Music, in the Music Library of Yale University.</p>
      </prefercite>
      <arrangement id="aspace_82739209e05c50407f023a2df5dce854">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>The collection is arranged alphabetically by surname of interviewee.</p>
      </arrangement>
